SUMMARY
The following summary is not prepared by the sponsors of the measure and is not a part of the body thereof subject
to consideration by the Legislative Assembly. It is an editor’s brief statement of the essential features of the
measure. The statement includes a measure digest written in compliance with applicable readability standards.
Digest: The Act changes the effective date and notice given for some agencies’ rules. The Act
tells some agencies to let people know where to ask questions about the agencies’ rules. (Flesch
Readability Score: 67.5).
Modifies effective date and notice requirements for certain permanent rules adopted, amended
or repealed by certain agencies.
Requires certain agencies to make available on the agency’s website contact information for
questions about each rule adopted, amended or repealed.
Takes effect on the 91st day following adjournment sine die.
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT
2 Relating to administrative rules; and prescribing an effective date.
3 Whereas state agencies routinely adopt administrative rules that impose new compliance obli-
4 gations or expose regulated entities to penalties for noncompliance; and
5 Whereas under current law, most administrative rules become effective immediately upon filing
6 with the Secretary of State unless a later effective date is specified; and
7 Whereas the immediate effectiveness of new rules may not provide regulated entities sufficient
8 time to understand, implement and comply with new requirements after they have been finalized;
9 now, therefore,
10 Be It Enacted by the People of the State of Oregon:
11 SECTION 1. Sections 2 and 3 of this 2026 Act are added to and made a part of ORS
12 chapter 183.
13 SECTION 2. (1) This section applies to the following agencies:
14 (a) The Environmental Quality Commission.
15 (b) The Oregon Transportation Commission.
16 (c) The State Land Board.
17 (d) The Department of State Lands.
18 (e) The governing board of the State Department of Geology and Mineral Industries.
19 (2) Notwithstanding ORS 183.355 (3), a permanent rule adopted, amended or repealed by
20 an agency listed in subsection (1) of this section that creates or modifies compliance re-
21 quirements for persons regulated by the agency may take effect no earlier than 28 days after
22 the date the final rule is filed with the Secretary of State as provided in ORS 183.355.
23 (3) Notwithstanding ORS 183.335 (1), prior to the adoption, amendment or repeal of a
