1 permanent rule, an agency listed in subsection (1) of this section shall give notice of its in-
2 tended action:
3 (a) In the manner established by rule adopted by the agency under ORS 183.341 (4), which
4 provides a reasonable opportunity for interested persons to be notified of the agency’s pro-
5 posed action;
6 (b) In the bulletin referred to in ORS 183.360 at least 21 days prior to the date the rule
7 is filed with the Secretary of State as provided in ORS 183.355;
8 (c) At least 28 days before the date the rule is filed with the Secretary of State as pro-
9 vided in ORS 183.355, to persons who have requested notice pursuant to ORS 183.335 (8); and
10 (d) Delivered only by email, at least 49 days before the date the rule is filed with the
11 Secretary of State as provided in ORS 183.355, to the persons specified in ORS 183.335 (15).
12 (4) This section does not apply to adoption, amendment or suspension of a rule under
13 ORS 183.335 (5).
14 SECTION 3. The following agencies shall make available on the agency’s website contact
15 information for questions about each rule adopted, amended or repealed by the agency:
16 (1) The Department of Environmental Quality.
17 (2) The Department of Transportation.
18 (3) The Department of State Lands.
19 (4) The State Department of Energy.
20 (5) The State Department of Geology and Mineral Industries.
21 SECTION 4. (1) Section 2 (2) of this 2026 Act applies to adoptions, amendments and re-
22 peals of rules with an effective date on or after January 1, 2027.
23 (2) Section 2 (3) of this 2026 Act applies to adoptions, amendments and repeals of rules
24 for which an agency provides notice of intended action on or after the effective date of this
25 2026 Act.
26 SECTION 5. This 2026 Act takes effect on the 91st day after the date on which the 2026
27 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly adjourns sine die.
